1
00:00:00,520 --> 00:00:01,890
I came up with three more proposals

2
00:00:01,890 --> 00:00:04,620
than this guy.

3
00:00:04,640 --> 00:00:06,570
Quality over quantity.

4
00:00:06,590 --> 00:00:09,170
Churning out useless proposals
is just wasted effort.

5
00:00:09,170 --> 00:00:11,620
Their rivalry is legendary
in the Sales Dept.

6
00:00:11,620 --> 00:00:13,720
The moment an opportunity appears,

7
00:00:13,720 --> 00:00:15,130
they'll do anything to one-up each other.

8
00:00:15,130 --> 00:00:16,800
What's even going on here?

9
00:00:17,100 --> 00:00:19,150
It's a face-off.

10
00:00:19,170 --> 00:00:21,500
One you started.

11
00:00:21,520 --> 00:00:22,660
What are you doing?

12
00:00:22,680 --> 00:00:24,140
Wait!

13
00:00:25,230 --> 00:00:26,050
Okay.

14
00:00:27,260 --> 00:00:28,760
I won.

15
00:00:29,800 --> 00:00:31,450
What a disaster.

16
00:00:31,480 --> 00:00:32,680
I'm going home.

17
00:00:32,700 --> 00:00:33,890
Hey!

18
00:00:36,640 --> 00:00:38,960
I haven't finished yet.

19
00:01:05,590 --> 00:01:07,060
You okay?

20
00:01:08,680 --> 00:01:09,710
Shut up.

21
00:01:10,090 --> 00:01:13,710
You're the one who got me like this,
and you still have the nerve to say that?

22
00:01:13,710 --> 00:01:15,030
You're right.

23
00:01:19,130 --> 00:01:21,810
If your body ends up needing me,

24
00:01:21,840 --> 00:01:23,170
I apologize in advance.

25
00:01:23,180 --> 00:01:24,110
That was my line.

26
00:01:24,820 --> 00:01:28,660
If you end up falling for me and can't be
with women anymore, don't blame me.

27
00:01:28,660 --> 00:01:29,800
What?

28
00:01:30,670 --> 00:01:33,120
You're the one who's going to fall for me.

29
00:01:35,340 --> 00:01:38,120
As if I'd ever fall for you.

30
00:01:38,940 --> 00:01:40,670
That's what I should be saying.

31
00:01:44,259 --> 00:01:45,140
Then...

32
00:01:46,670 --> 00:01:47,500
Shall we?

33
00:01:47,520 --> 00:01:48,170
What?

34
00:01:49,479 --> 00:01:51,280
Let's have a face-off over this.

35
00:01:53,789 --> 00:01:55,320
Gladly.

36
00:01:56,920 --> 00:01:57,960
Then,

37
00:01:58,340 --> 00:02:01,000
whoever makes the other
fall in love first wins.

38
00:02:01,410 --> 00:02:02,900
Deal.

39
00:02:25,390 --> 00:02:25,940
Eh?

40
00:02:26,520 --> 00:02:27,340
Onishi,

41
00:02:27,360 --> 00:02:29,820
is there material about the trailer
in here?

42
00:02:30,770 --> 00:02:31,370
Hm?

43
00:02:33,490 --> 00:02:34,770
Higashino?

44
00:02:35,570 --> 00:02:37,540
Hey, we need to reprint this again!

45
00:02:37,560 --> 00:02:39,290
Sorry, I'll redo it right away!

46
00:02:39,810 --> 00:02:40,670
I'm sorry.

47
00:02:41,200 --> 00:02:43,120
It's fine. There's still time.

48
00:02:43,590 --> 00:02:44,450
Ah.

49
00:02:44,980 --> 00:02:47,930
I need to prepare another set of materials.
I'll head to the meeting room first.

50
00:02:47,930 --> 00:02:48,840
Call me if anything comes up.

51
00:02:48,840 --> 00:02:49,660
Got it.

52
00:02:51,190 --> 00:02:52,230
You okay?

53
00:02:53,250 --> 00:02:54,300
I can help.

54
00:02:54,590 --> 00:02:56,400
It'll be done soon. It's okay.

55
00:02:56,730 --> 00:02:57,550
You'd better

56
00:02:57,990 --> 00:02:59,560
help Higashino instead.

57
00:02:59,940 --> 00:03:01,600
-Okay.
-I'll leave him to you.

58
00:03:06,680 --> 00:03:07,180
[Contents]

59
00:03:07,650 --> 00:03:11,000
[The Importance of SNS Operations]

60
00:03:18,600 --> 00:03:19,180
Hey,

61
00:03:20,010 --> 00:03:21,740
preparing for a presentation?

62
00:03:35,740 --> 00:03:37,930
Hey, Yotsuya!

63
00:03:37,950 --> 00:03:39,870
We had fun last night, right?

64
00:03:40,900 --> 00:03:42,740
Um, yeah.

65
00:03:43,090 --> 00:03:44,460
Really.

66
00:03:44,480 --> 00:03:47,190
I never get tired of being with you.

67
00:03:47,220 --> 00:03:49,440
Oh, right.

68
00:03:51,079 --> 00:03:53,030
Why did you suddenly call me?

69
00:03:53,810 --> 00:03:55,360
Hm? What do you mean?

70
00:03:57,140 --> 00:03:59,310
Well, it's a bit sudden,

71
00:03:59,329 --> 00:04:00,990
but are you free this weekend?

72
00:04:01,010 --> 00:04:02,090
This weekend?

73
00:04:02,400 --> 00:04:03,580
Hold on.

74
00:04:03,720 --> 00:04:06,400
This weekend...

75
00:04:08,370 --> 00:04:08,940
I'm free.

76
00:04:09,260 --> 00:04:10,180
Then, good.

77
00:04:10,200 --> 00:04:12,360
The restaurant I went to for work before

78
00:04:12,360 --> 00:04:15,010
has a nice view,
and the food is delicious.

79
00:04:15,650 --> 00:04:16,510
Want to go together?

80
00:04:16,510 --> 00:04:20,560
Oh, asking me out on a date already?

81
00:04:21,540 --> 00:04:22,970
Then, should we book a hotel too?

82
00:04:22,970 --> 00:04:23,490
What?

83
00:04:24,340 --> 00:04:25,740
You, on the other hand...

84
00:04:26,090 --> 00:04:27,290
Are you feeling okay?

85
00:04:28,040 --> 00:04:29,370
Keep your hands to yourself!

86
00:04:29,370 --> 00:04:30,550
What's wrong?

87
00:04:30,580 --> 00:04:32,640
Are you being emotionally unstable?

88
00:04:35,030 --> 00:04:36,900
Can't you be a little nicer to me?

89
00:04:38,880 --> 00:04:41,010
We've already spent a night together.

90
00:04:42,170 --> 00:04:43,170
Stay away from me!

91
00:04:46,920 --> 00:04:48,180
You know...

92
00:04:49,140 --> 00:04:51,850
you're so erratic
when it comes to romance.

93
00:04:52,610 --> 00:04:55,220
-What?
-You're so capable at work,

94
00:04:55,370 --> 00:04:59,340
but your relationship skills
might still be at a high schooler's level.

95
00:04:59,340 --> 00:05:00,320
Hey,

96
00:05:00,590 --> 00:05:03,450
-do you know how popular I've been...
-But still...

97
00:05:05,480 --> 00:05:07,140
that side of you is kinda cute.

98
00:05:08,240 --> 00:05:09,470
Stop teasing me!

99
00:05:15,040 --> 00:05:16,270
Then...

100
00:05:17,870 --> 00:05:18,600
How do you...

101
00:05:20,100 --> 00:05:22,930
usually seduce men?

102
00:05:23,770 --> 00:05:24,470
What?

103
00:05:26,020 --> 00:05:27,540
I mean...

104
00:05:28,740 --> 00:05:29,860
I want to know how you do it.

105
00:05:29,860 --> 00:05:30,630
Well,

106
00:05:31,690 --> 00:05:33,290
I've been meaning to ask you—

107
00:05:34,130 --> 00:05:35,400
why do you always assume
I've been hooking up with guys?

108
00:05:35,400 --> 00:05:36,680
Eh?

109
00:05:39,050 --> 00:05:40,930
I haven't done that before

110
00:05:41,260 --> 00:05:42,290
with any man

111
00:05:42,740 --> 00:05:43,840
other than you.

112
00:05:47,110 --> 00:05:48,480
What?

113
00:05:49,260 --> 00:05:50,560
No, but at that time, you...

114
00:05:50,560 --> 00:05:52,560
The presentation's about to start.

115
00:06:02,860 --> 00:06:03,790
Seriously?

116
00:07:04,500 --> 00:07:08,450
[Fake Fact Lips]

117
00:07:09,800 --> 00:07:13,880
[Episode 2: Then I Won't Hold Back]

118
00:07:11,300 --> 00:07:12,100
Thank you.

119
00:07:12,120 --> 00:07:13,310
Thank you.

120
00:07:22,360 --> 00:07:24,840
-Good work.
-Good work.

121
00:07:25,100 --> 00:07:26,830
Honestly, Mr. Shido, you were incredible.

122
00:07:26,830 --> 00:07:30,200
I really thought we were going to
come out on the losing end this time.

123
00:07:30,200 --> 00:07:32,280
That counterattack was amazing.

124
00:07:32,430 --> 00:07:34,420
Did you see through their strategy?

125
00:07:34,420 --> 00:07:36,710
Not exactly. But that kind of maneuvering
is very important.

126
00:07:36,710 --> 00:07:37,580
In negotiations like that,

127
00:07:37,580 --> 00:07:40,140
if you try to prioritize
the other party's interests first,

128
00:07:40,140 --> 00:07:42,800
you may unexpectedly find
it benefits your own.

129
00:07:42,890 --> 00:07:43,780
I see.

130
00:07:44,110 --> 00:07:45,640
Just like dating.

131
00:07:46,630 --> 00:07:47,150
What?

132
00:07:47,590 --> 00:07:48,820
What do you mean?

133
00:07:49,080 --> 00:07:49,940
Like,

134
00:07:50,140 --> 00:07:52,040
instead of only thinking about yourself,

135
00:07:52,040 --> 00:07:54,820
if you focus on doing things
that make the other person happy,

136
00:07:54,820 --> 00:07:56,460
it naturally brings good results

137
00:07:56,460 --> 00:07:58,640
for yourself too.

138
00:07:58,670 --> 00:07:59,870
Something like that.

139
00:08:00,020 --> 00:08:00,990
Onishi.

140
00:08:01,310 --> 00:08:01,720
Yes.

141
00:08:02,710 --> 00:08:03,570
I see.

142
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:05,330
What do you mean by that?

143
00:08:05,460 --> 00:08:07,600
Mr. Shido, you're just on another level.

144
00:08:07,600 --> 00:08:10,600
You can handle
both work and romance with ease, right?

145
00:08:10,950 --> 00:08:11,820
I...

146
00:08:12,770 --> 00:08:13,810
have never

147
00:08:14,120 --> 00:08:16,070
actually pursued someone myself.

148
00:08:16,100 --> 00:08:17,170
Oh?

149
00:08:19,420 --> 00:08:21,940
How would you make someone
you don't actually like

150
00:08:21,940 --> 00:08:22,850
fall for you?

151
00:08:22,880 --> 00:08:25,930
-Huh?
-Someone you don't like?

152
00:08:25,990 --> 00:08:27,720
Yeah, but...

153
00:08:27,830 --> 00:08:29,720
I must get them.

154
00:08:30,880 --> 00:08:32,140
What do you mean?

155
00:08:32,240 --> 00:08:34,169
That sounds really hard.

156
00:08:34,530 --> 00:08:35,850
But that's exactly why

157
00:08:36,640 --> 00:08:39,770
you have to think about
what's in it for the other person,

158
00:08:39,850 --> 00:08:41,419
do research,

159
00:08:42,490 --> 00:08:45,710
and focus entirely on
what would make them happy—

160
00:08:45,840 --> 00:08:47,040
something like that?

161
00:08:49,020 --> 00:08:50,510
Um, Mr. Shido,

162
00:08:51,540 --> 00:08:55,270
somehow this conversation is starting to
sound very problematic.

163
00:08:55,280 --> 00:08:55,920
What?

164
00:08:56,390 --> 00:08:57,130
This isn't some kind of

165
00:08:57,130 --> 00:08:58,080
quid pro quo, right?

166
00:08:58,080 --> 00:08:59,120
No.

167
00:08:59,140 --> 00:09:00,630
Of course not.

168
00:09:00,650 --> 00:09:02,640
It's all your fault—
you asked such a weird question!

169
00:09:02,640 --> 00:09:05,450
Well, but it's still worth referencing.
Thank you.

170
00:09:05,450 --> 00:09:07,050
I'll head to the meeting now.

171
00:09:12,960 --> 00:09:14,290
What's all that about?

172
00:09:21,690 --> 00:09:22,860
Ah.

173
00:09:28,550 --> 00:09:31,780
Alright, time to go home.

174
00:09:43,580 --> 00:09:45,070
It's okay. You can go back first.

175
00:09:45,070 --> 00:09:46,510
No, but...

176
00:09:46,530 --> 00:09:47,760
Don't worry about it.

177
00:09:48,460 --> 00:09:51,080
Okay, I'll head out then.

178
00:09:51,100 --> 00:09:52,350
See you tomorrow.

179
00:09:52,370 --> 00:09:53,010
Okay.

180
00:10:32,940 --> 00:10:34,590
So cold!

181
00:10:34,820 --> 00:10:35,840
Good work today.

182
00:10:36,560 --> 00:10:37,270
What?

183
00:10:37,690 --> 00:10:39,090
You're still here too?

184
00:10:39,450 --> 00:10:40,620
It's rare to see you
still working at this hour.

185
00:10:40,620 --> 00:10:41,800
Sort of.

186
00:10:42,740 --> 00:10:43,670
Need something?

187
00:10:46,390 --> 00:10:48,030
Are you here to woo me?

188
00:10:49,020 --> 00:10:50,840
I'm exhausted right now.

189
00:10:50,860 --> 00:10:52,430
-No. Well...
-Hm?

190
00:10:55,480 --> 00:10:57,610
It's about what you said this morning.

191
00:10:58,670 --> 00:10:59,350
What was it?

192
00:11:01,420 --> 00:11:04,170
Well... You know...

193
00:11:06,850 --> 00:11:07,650
What exactly?

194
00:11:09,240 --> 00:11:12,570
That thing you said about
it being your first time with a guy.

195
00:11:12,920 --> 00:11:14,070
So what?

196
00:11:16,990 --> 00:11:18,120
So it was true.

197
00:11:19,130 --> 00:11:21,900
Huh? Why would I lie?

198
00:11:22,850 --> 00:11:23,970
But you...

199
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:29,040
What?

200
00:11:30,220 --> 00:11:31,920
That was your first time.

201
00:11:32,210 --> 00:11:34,730
-Yet you were way too seductive.
-Idiot!

202
00:11:34,750 --> 00:11:35,950
Keep your voice down.

203
00:11:36,870 --> 00:11:39,240
But you were the one saying

204
00:11:39,950 --> 00:11:41,630
you weren't against
doing that kind of thing

205
00:11:41,630 --> 00:11:43,060
with a guy.

206
00:11:43,200 --> 00:11:46,210
That was obviously just me bluffing.

207
00:11:46,240 --> 00:11:48,210
Then you should've

208
00:11:48,480 --> 00:11:49,690
pushed back more.

209
00:11:50,330 --> 00:11:53,100
You didn't give me a chance to say no.

210
00:11:53,130 --> 00:11:54,460
Even so...

211
00:11:54,990 --> 00:11:56,000
Anyway...

212
00:12:01,590 --> 00:12:02,380
What?

213
00:12:04,350 --> 00:12:05,480
I'd never let anyone

214
00:12:05,560 --> 00:12:06,690
do that to me but you.

215
00:12:10,630 --> 00:12:12,940
By the way, have you done it before?

216
00:12:14,670 --> 00:12:15,280
Well...

217
00:12:16,670 --> 00:12:18,520
I did.

218
00:12:19,180 --> 00:12:20,950
When? Tell me.

219
00:12:21,700 --> 00:12:22,620
In high school?

220
00:12:22,640 --> 00:12:23,760
No.

221
00:12:23,780 --> 00:12:24,700
In college...

222
00:12:25,130 --> 00:12:27,130
Can we drop that?

223
00:12:28,150 --> 00:12:29,150
You're

224
00:12:29,590 --> 00:12:31,320
actually pretty popular with guys, huh?

225
00:12:31,320 --> 00:12:32,720
Shut up.

226
00:12:32,740 --> 00:12:35,940
I just thought
things were simpler with guys, that's all.

227
00:12:37,740 --> 00:12:38,940
Then, that night,

228
00:12:39,180 --> 00:12:41,420
you were turned on
by my body, weren't you?

229
00:12:41,420 --> 00:12:42,500
Huh?

230
00:12:43,250 --> 00:12:43,980
Then,

231
00:12:45,220 --> 00:12:46,750
want a repeat of last night?

232
00:12:47,400 --> 00:12:48,130
You've

233
00:12:48,630 --> 00:12:51,160
got some nerve
saying that for a straight guy.

234
00:12:52,190 --> 00:12:53,250
Aren't you scared?

235
00:12:53,740 --> 00:12:54,850
I've already done it once.

236
00:12:54,850 --> 00:12:56,280
The second or third time
shouldn't make a difference, right?

237
00:12:56,280 --> 00:12:57,980
How could it be the same?

238
00:12:59,630 --> 00:13:01,360
You're really something else.

239
00:13:04,200 --> 00:13:05,230
I...

240
00:13:06,170 --> 00:13:08,430
am not planning on being your sex friend.

241
00:13:09,800 --> 00:13:12,900
So what else do you enjoy then?

242
00:13:12,920 --> 00:13:14,720
Why are you suddenly asking that?

243
00:13:14,720 --> 00:13:17,720
Who even asks their high school buddy
stuff like that?

244
00:13:19,580 --> 00:13:21,510
Well, I wasn't interested before.

245
00:13:28,480 --> 00:13:29,690
I...

246
00:13:31,270 --> 00:13:32,490
want to know

247
00:13:33,580 --> 00:13:35,180
more about you. Everything.

248
00:13:36,950 --> 00:13:38,980
We've always been too busy
competing with each other.

249
00:13:37,690 --> 00:13:39,780
[Exam Ranking List]

250
00:13:39,670 --> 00:13:42,600
We've never really
talked about ourselves, have we?

251
00:13:51,210 --> 00:13:52,670
Let's take this chance...

252
00:13:54,620 --> 00:13:56,620
to get a little closer to each other.

253
00:13:57,760 --> 00:13:58,490
So?

254
00:13:59,150 --> 00:14:00,840
You think
I'll just fall for you like that?

255
00:14:00,840 --> 00:14:03,380
Well... I can't say for sure.

256
00:14:05,340 --> 00:14:06,670
I'll make you...

257
00:14:08,230 --> 00:14:09,170
fall for me.

258
00:14:11,030 --> 00:14:12,760
You're like an idiot right now.

259
00:14:14,060 --> 00:14:17,260
It's only fun if you go all in
like a complete idiot, right?

260
00:14:17,330 --> 00:14:18,090
Oh?

261
00:14:18,820 --> 00:14:20,200
Don't tell me

262
00:14:21,650 --> 00:14:24,050
you're actually afraid you'll fall for me.

263
00:14:24,280 --> 00:14:25,620
As if!

264
00:14:25,880 --> 00:14:26,980
I should be saying that.

265
00:14:26,980 --> 00:14:29,710
Struggling now that you can't
sleep with anyone but me, huh?

266
00:14:29,710 --> 00:14:30,860
What?

267
00:14:30,880 --> 00:14:32,640
If you have the guts...

268
00:14:35,990 --> 00:14:36,870
Then...

269
00:14:38,340 --> 00:14:39,380
I won't hold back.

270
00:14:56,600 --> 00:14:57,360
Oh,

271
00:14:57,380 --> 00:14:58,800
perfect timing.

272
00:14:59,870 --> 00:15:00,770
Cabernet.

273
00:15:01,130 --> 00:15:02,330
You like this, right?

274
00:15:02,850 --> 00:15:03,680
Hey, hey.

275
00:15:04,320 --> 00:15:05,400
How did you know?

276
00:15:05,640 --> 00:15:06,380
Well.

277
00:15:07,280 --> 00:15:09,040
You always order Cabernet

278
00:15:09,380 --> 00:15:10,890
at client dinners, don't you?

279
00:15:10,890 --> 00:15:11,890
That's how I know.

280
00:15:12,950 --> 00:15:13,490
Ah.

281
00:15:14,030 --> 00:15:14,470
Sit.

282
00:15:16,260 --> 00:15:17,520
I like the wine, but...

283
00:15:18,390 --> 00:15:20,610
Having a glass of this after a bath—

284
00:15:20,710 --> 00:15:22,530
now that's the life.

285
00:15:24,410 --> 00:15:26,270
What exactly are you trying to do?

286
00:15:26,440 --> 00:15:27,530
Also,

287
00:15:28,100 --> 00:15:30,300
you've been really busy lately, right?

288
00:15:31,170 --> 00:15:33,970
I think you might want to
unwind like this tonight.

289
00:15:42,880 --> 00:15:43,940
Cheers.

290
00:15:54,840 --> 00:15:55,880
Besides,

291
00:15:57,070 --> 00:15:57,870
you'll

292
00:15:57,900 --> 00:16:01,360
also be participating in the launch
of the new project, right?

293
00:16:03,540 --> 00:16:06,200
Zen, you've never really
been good at relaxing.

294
00:16:08,480 --> 00:16:10,210
Destressing is important too.

295
00:16:11,100 --> 00:16:12,980
You're the one who stresses me out.

296
00:16:12,980 --> 00:16:14,380
Even back in high school,

297
00:16:14,840 --> 00:16:18,240
you always looked like
it would kill you not to top every exam.

298
00:16:18,610 --> 00:16:19,600
And always...

299
00:16:20,610 --> 00:16:22,430
frowning so hard.

300
00:16:22,460 --> 00:16:23,230
Stop it.

301
00:16:23,250 --> 00:16:25,120
That's because you kept provoking me.

302
00:16:25,120 --> 00:16:27,450
This stubborn competitive side of you...

303
00:16:29,120 --> 00:16:30,330
is pretty cute too.

304
00:16:30,950 --> 00:16:32,310
Cut the sweet talk.

305
00:16:32,590 --> 00:16:34,320
We're in a face-off, aren't we?

306
00:16:39,520 --> 00:16:41,250
You're not only good-looking,

307
00:16:42,060 --> 00:16:44,110
but also really manly.

308
00:16:46,040 --> 00:16:46,810
Honestly...

309
00:16:49,310 --> 00:16:50,640
I've never met

310
00:16:51,440 --> 00:16:52,500
anyone like you.

311
00:17:02,170 --> 00:17:02,650
Ryo.

312
00:17:05,630 --> 00:17:07,990
You're really not honest with yourself.

313
00:17:08,670 --> 00:17:09,500
What do you mean?

314
00:17:09,500 --> 00:17:11,170
If you felt that way,

315
00:17:11,190 --> 00:17:13,050
you could've just told me sooner.

316
00:17:15,960 --> 00:17:16,609
But

317
00:17:18,119 --> 00:17:19,609
it's not just my face...

318
00:17:21,760 --> 00:17:24,000
you like my body too, right?

319
00:17:27,880 --> 00:17:29,150
Just be honest.

320
00:17:30,450 --> 00:17:33,460
For you, I might make
a special exception.

321
00:17:37,150 --> 00:17:38,150
What do you think?

322
00:17:39,330 --> 00:17:40,450
Let's start with your hand...

323
00:17:40,450 --> 00:17:41,960
Not like this.

324
00:17:42,790 --> 00:17:43,650
Why?

325
00:17:44,570 --> 00:17:47,170
Didn't you just say
destressing is important?

326
00:17:47,840 --> 00:17:48,790
Yeah.

327
00:17:50,110 --> 00:17:52,840
Do you know
that kissing can also relieve stress?

328
00:17:53,830 --> 00:17:56,370
Yeah, I've heard that.

329
00:17:58,020 --> 00:17:59,940
Even so, can you...

330
00:18:05,460 --> 00:18:06,860
Don't underestimate me.

331
00:18:07,030 --> 00:18:08,690
It's just a kiss. No big deal.

332
00:18:10,360 --> 00:18:11,450
Well...

333
00:18:35,620 --> 00:18:37,240
If you want to get me...

334
00:18:39,300 --> 00:18:41,230
you'll have to at least go this far.

335
00:18:50,200 --> 00:18:50,870
Zen?

336
00:19:01,670 --> 00:19:02,950
Hurry up.

337
00:19:03,060 --> 00:19:04,190
Let's eat together.

338
00:19:04,500 --> 00:19:06,270
I bought your lunch—isn't that enough?

339
00:19:06,270 --> 00:19:07,930
Why do we have to eat together?

340
00:19:09,320 --> 00:19:10,160
Ah.

341
00:19:11,020 --> 00:19:12,910
You always eat alone.

342
00:19:12,930 --> 00:19:15,730
It's nice to do this
every once in a while, isn't it?

343
00:19:16,050 --> 00:19:19,250
This is exactly why I prefer eating alone—
I don't like it.

344
00:19:19,640 --> 00:19:21,270
Doesn't the winner

345
00:19:21,530 --> 00:19:23,030
get to call the shots?

346
00:19:23,890 --> 00:19:25,260
Since when was that a rule?

347
00:19:25,260 --> 00:19:26,520
Just now.

348
00:19:27,060 --> 00:19:27,980
I'm digging in.

349
00:19:45,300 --> 00:19:46,060
Hey, Zen.

350
00:19:47,440 --> 00:19:49,570
Don't just call me by my name like that.

351
00:19:53,320 --> 00:19:54,330
Do you...

352
00:19:55,500 --> 00:19:57,100
stay this tense even at home?

353
00:19:58,220 --> 00:19:59,150
What do you mean?

354
00:20:00,510 --> 00:20:02,050
It feels like you're always

355
00:20:02,070 --> 00:20:03,530
so wrapped up in studying.

356
00:20:04,300 --> 00:20:06,120
If you don't relax every now and then,

357
00:20:06,120 --> 00:20:07,050
you'll burn out.

358
00:20:08,890 --> 00:20:10,200
I do relax.

359
00:20:11,860 --> 00:20:12,920
How?

360
00:20:14,660 --> 00:20:15,690
When I get home...

361
00:20:15,710 --> 00:20:16,450
Hm.

362
00:20:16,470 --> 00:20:17,600
I take a shower.

363
00:20:17,920 --> 00:20:18,210
Okay.

364
00:20:18,210 --> 00:20:20,140
Then just lie there and do nothing.

365
00:20:21,130 --> 00:20:21,770
That's it?

366
00:20:23,150 --> 00:20:25,060
Well, that's when I'm home alone.

367
00:20:34,730 --> 00:20:35,580
Why are you asking this, anyway?

368
00:20:35,580 --> 00:20:37,510
Look—your brow's furrowed again.

369
00:20:38,000 --> 00:20:39,110
Don't touch me.

370
00:20:39,130 --> 00:20:40,860
You've got crumbs on your face.

371
00:20:41,700 --> 00:20:42,750
You're so rude.

372
00:20:43,740 --> 00:20:45,940
Next time, try lying down after eating.

373
00:20:46,310 --> 00:20:46,760
Hey.

374
00:20:46,780 --> 00:20:49,000
That's just being a slob.

375
00:20:49,030 --> 00:20:50,600
Come on.

376
00:20:50,630 --> 00:20:52,450
Come on! Lie down.

377
00:21:02,280 --> 00:21:04,560
-Right?
-What?

378
00:21:06,690 --> 00:21:08,420
Someone as hardworking as you

379
00:21:08,820 --> 00:21:11,680
isn't going to turn into
a slob just from doing this.

380
00:21:12,330 --> 00:21:13,170
This is...

381
00:21:13,690 --> 00:21:14,700
relaxing.

382
00:21:29,530 --> 00:21:30,330
Oh.

383
00:21:31,820 --> 00:21:33,130
You slept so soundly.

384
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:36,340
Let go...

385
00:21:36,370 --> 00:21:37,860
Zen, you know what?

386
00:21:38,830 --> 00:21:41,410
Hugging relieves stress too.

387
00:21:41,440 --> 00:21:44,120
This is the most stressful time
for me right now!

388
00:21:44,150 --> 00:21:46,210
Sorry, I didn't notice.

389
00:21:47,760 --> 00:21:50,650
After working that hard,
of course, you'd fall asleep

390
00:21:50,650 --> 00:21:52,570
once you relaxed.

391
00:21:53,680 --> 00:21:54,350
Besides,

392
00:21:55,310 --> 00:21:57,360
that kiss earlier
got you more worked up, didn't it?

393
00:21:57,360 --> 00:21:58,540
No, it didn't!

394
00:22:00,190 --> 00:22:01,380
For you,

395
00:22:02,280 --> 00:22:04,790
a hug like this is just what you need.

396
00:22:05,070 --> 00:22:06,150
I told you...

397
00:22:06,680 --> 00:22:08,640
All I felt was stress.

398
00:22:09,490 --> 00:22:12,270
Says the guy who suddenly kissed me.

399
00:22:19,460 --> 00:22:20,440
Yeah, yeah.

400
00:22:20,930 --> 00:22:22,570
That's more like it.

401
00:22:27,280 --> 00:22:27,810
Eh?

402
00:22:29,740 --> 00:22:30,800
Fell asleep again?

403
00:22:34,170 --> 00:22:35,280
Ryo.

404
00:22:36,250 --> 00:22:36,620
Hm?

405
00:22:38,570 --> 00:22:40,290
Did you use to

406
00:22:40,980 --> 00:22:43,040
pursue all kinds of people like this?

407
00:22:51,040 --> 00:22:51,700
Somehow...

408
00:22:54,830 --> 00:22:56,960
I can't help feeling a little jealous.

409
00:22:58,770 --> 00:22:59,710
From now on,

410
00:23:01,230 --> 00:23:03,560
you're only allowed to
be this way with me.

411
00:23:04,410 --> 00:23:04,840
Got it?

412
00:23:09,720 --> 00:23:10,230
Zen.

413
00:23:12,820 --> 00:23:13,470
I...

414
00:23:13,490 --> 00:23:15,320
You think I'd say something like that?

415
00:23:15,320 --> 00:23:16,210
Idiot!

416
00:23:17,360 --> 00:23:18,220
I'm going home!

417
00:23:19,150 --> 00:23:19,940
Wait!

418
00:23:20,830 --> 00:23:21,830
Stay the night!

419
00:23:21,850 --> 00:23:23,830
No. Who'd want to stay?

420
00:23:47,490 --> 00:23:48,120
Bye.

421
00:24:11,850 --> 00:24:18,120
[That's good. Don't get the hotel wrong.]

422
00:24:35,700 --> 00:24:41,850
[As if I would. See you then.]

423
00:25:46,590 --> 00:25:48,970
[In the Next Episode]

424
00:25:47,160 --> 00:25:48,360
If you're confident,

425
00:25:49,000 --> 00:25:52,760
[Episode 3:
I Said Only With Me, Didn't I?]

426
00:25:49,980 --> 00:25:51,390
try pursuing me again.

427
00:25:51,420 --> 00:25:53,330
She asked me out

428
00:25:53,350 --> 00:25:55,150
for drinks later.

429
00:25:55,170 --> 00:25:56,800
You really can't judge a book by its cover.
She's quite the huntress.

430
00:25:56,800 --> 00:25:57,770
Oh, Mr. Shido!

431
00:25:57,790 --> 00:25:59,930
Thank you for coming today.

432
00:25:59,950 --> 00:26:01,470
-Do you know each other?
-Do you know each other?

433
00:26:01,470 --> 00:26:03,370
Has something happened
between you and Mr. Yotsuya?

434
00:26:03,370 --> 00:26:04,520
Don't get too close to me!

435
00:26:04,520 --> 00:26:05,440
Shut up.

436
00:26:05,470 --> 00:26:06,660
What?

437
00:26:07,680 --> 00:26:10,180
-Stop it.
-You reacted.

438
00:26:10,200 --> 00:26:12,360
I'm Yotsuya. Nice to meet you.

439
00:26:11,380 --> 00:26:16,500
[Exam Ranking List]
